    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1060"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1060">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/5–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Syrian Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mardam</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="37" xml:id="d1060fn37">Original message transmitted to the Department
                        on May 24 by M. C. Latta, Executive Clerk of the White House, and returned
                        to him on June 21 with a translation and a copy of the Acting Secretary’s
                        reply, telegram 161 of May 30, <ref target="#pg_1115">p. 1115</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-23">May 23,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Syrian Government handed your Minister Damascus copy French <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi> formulating demands absolutely incompatible Syrian
                    sovereignty independence as well as copy note in reply Syrian Government
                    protesting against influx French troops and refusing any discussion on bases.
                        <hi rend="italic">Aide-mémoire</hi> your Government had recognized Syrian
                    independence and excluded granting any privilege. Now France asks privileges
                    infringing on independence and legitimate rights Syria. Anxious to maintain
                    order Near East and not to have recourse to extreme measures of nature to open
                    new phases of bloody hostilities after end of war in Europe Syrian Government
                    solicits use of your benevolent intervention in order to induce France to
                    withdraw troops and respect Syrian sovereignty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jamil Mardam</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
